Student Support Programs Students have an advisory period twice a week to help ensure that they are successful both academically and socially. The school holds weekly SAP (Students Assistance Program) meetings to talk about any students who may be struggling academically or socially to make sure they have access to the necessary services.
Student Support Programs Student Study Team, Lunchtime Wellness Program, Tutorial/Homework Clubs
LSP/Social Worker who is supported by Student Counselors and is available to assist identified children (and families) with emotional, developmental and situational issues. Our LSP is also a resource to teachers, staff and families.
Student Support Services SCVP, TUPE, Mentoring, Youth Outreach Worker (YOW) program addressing tobacco & alcohol prevention. HIFY is Health Initiative for Youth. Various psycho/educational groups depending on student need
